  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HCFC Phase-out Management Plan Stage-II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Executive Committee of the Multilateral Fund for the Implementation of the Montreal Protocol, at its 63rd  Meeting, approved stage I of the HCFC phase-out management plan (HPMP) for Benin to achieve the 35 %reduction in HCFC consumption by 2020

The Government had agreed to establish an estimated baseline of 23.6 ODP tonnes as its starting point for sustained aggregate reduction in HCFC consumption, calculated using consumption of 23.6 ODP tonnes reported for 2009 and consumption of 23.6 ODP tonnes estimated for 2010.

The Government of Benin committed to the following control measures with the support of funding and technical assistance from the Multilateral Fund and implementing agency:
(i) Freeze the consumption of HCFCs in 2013 to the agreed baseline figure;
(ii) (ii) Reduce consumption of HCFCs by 10% from 2015;
(iii) (iii) Reduce consumption of HCFCs by 35% by 2020.</narrative>
  </description>
